19}}\n}}\n\n==Playoff and finals==\n{{main|2020 Canadian Premier League Finals}}\nWith the change to a single table regular season comes a change to the post-season, with the introduction of a two-round play-off. The first place team in the regular season will qualify directly to the 2020 CPL Finals, while the second and third place teams will compete in a playoff to determine the second spot in the Finals.<ref>{{cite news |title=BEDAKIAN: Single-table, playoff soccer has come to the CPL \u2013 and it's beautiful |url=https://canpl.ca/article/bedakian-single-table-playoff-soccer-has-come-to-the-cpl-and-its-beautiful |accessdate=21 February 2020 |publisher=Canadian Premier League}}</ref>\n\n===Bracket===\n{{3TeamBracket\n|RD1 =[[2020 Canadian Premier League Finals#Playoff|Playoff]]\n|RD2 = [[2020 Canadian Premier League Finals|Finals]]\n|RD1-seed1 = 2\n|RD1-team1 = \n|RD1-score1 = \n|RD1-seed2 = 3\n|RD1-team2 = \n|RD1-score2 = \n|RD2-seed1 = 1\n|RD2-team1 = \n|RD2-score1 = \n|RD2-seed2 = &nbsp;\n|RD2-team2 = \n|RD2-score2 = \n}}\n\n== Player transfers ==\n{{Main|List of 2020 Canadian Premier League transfers|l1=Canadian Premier League transfers 2020}}\n\n=== U Sports Draft ===\n{{further|2019 CPL\u2013U Sports Draft}}\n\nThe [[2019 CPL\u2013U Sports Draft]] was held on November 11 in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]]. Draftees will be invited to team preseason camps, with an opportunity to earn a developmental contract and retain their [[U Sports men's soccer]] eligibility. [[HFX Wanderers FC|HFX Wanderers]] selected Cory Bent with the first overall pick. Two players were selected by each returning CPL team, with a total of 14 players being drafted including 10 Canadians.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/live-2019-cpl-u-sports-draft-tracker-follow-all-14-picks|title=TRACKER: All 14 picks from the 2019 CPL-U SPORTS Draft|date=November 11, 2019|website=Canadian Premier League|language=en-CA|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref> Ottawa had not yet joined the league and did not participate in the draft.\n\n=== Foreign players ===\nCanadian Premier League teams may sign a maximum of seven international players, out of which only five can be in the starting line-up for each match. The following players are considered foreign players for the 2020 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/cpl-off-season-roster-tracker-whos-in-and-whos-out-for-2020|title=CPL off-season roster tracker: Who's in and who's out for 2020?|date=November 4, 2019|website=Canadian Premier League|language=en-CA|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe list does not include Canadian citizens who represent other countries at the international level.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Club\n!Player 1\n!Player 2\n!Player 3\n!Player 4\n!Player 5\n!Player 6\n!Player 7\n|-\n|[[Atl\u00e9tico Ottawa]]\n|{{Flagicon|England}} [[Vashon Neufville]]\n|{{Flagicon|Jamaica}} [[Tevin Shaw]]\n|{{Flagicon|Mexico}} [[Francisco Acu\u00f1a]]\n|{{Flagicon|Ghana}} [[Bernardinho (footballer)|Bernardinho]]\n|{{Flagicon|Spain}} [[Ignacio Zabal|Nacho Zabal]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Cavalry FC|Cavalry]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} [[Oliver Minatel|Oliver]]\n|{{Flagicon|England}} [[Jordan Brown (footballer, born 1996)|Jordan Brown]]\n|{{Flagicon|Peru|football}} [[Jair C\u00f3rdova]]\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[Nathan Mavila]]\n|{{flagicon|Honduras}} [[Jos\u00e9 Escalante]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} [[Richard Luca]]\n|\n|-\n|[[FC Edmonton]]\n|{{Flagicon|Trinidad and Tobago}} [[Kareem Moses]]\n|{{Flagicon|Spain}} [[Ram\u00f3n Soria]]\n|{{Flagicon|Cameroon}} [[Jeannot Esua]]\n|{{Flagicon|South Korea}} [[Son Yong-chan]]\n|{{Flagicon|Sweden}} [[Erik Zetterberg]]\n|{{Flagicon|Peru|football}} [[Ra\u00fal Tito]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Forge FC|Forge]]\n|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Alexander Achinioti-J\u00f6nsson]]\n|{{flagicon|SEN}} [[Elimane Ciss\u00e9]]\n|{{flagicon|BEL}} [[Daniel Krutzen]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[HFX Wanderers FC|HFX Wanderers]] \n|{{Flagicon|Trinidad and Tobago}} [[Andre Rampersad]]\n|{{Flagicon|Trinidad and Tobago}} [[Akeem Garcia]]\n|{{Flagicon|Germany}} [[Peter Schaale]]\n|{{Flagicon|Jamaica}} [[Alex Marshall (footballer)|Alex Marshall]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} [[Eriks Santos]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} Jo\u00e3o Morelli\n|\n|-\n|[[Pacific FC|Pacific]]\n|{{Flagicon|Mexico}} [[Alejandro D\u00edaz Lice\u00e1ga|Alejandro D\u00edaz]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Valour FC|Valour]]\n|{{Flagicon|GHA}} Solomon Kojo Antwi\n|{{Flagicon|HAI}} [[Andrew Jean-Baptiste]]\n|{{Flagicon|PAN}} Amir Soto\n|{{Flagicon|NZL}} [[Moses Dyer]]\n|{{Flagicon|CGO}} [[Arnold Bouka Moutou]]\n|{{Flagicon|SPA}} [[Jos\u00e9 Gal\u00e1n]]\n|\n|-\n|[[York9 FC|York9]]\n|{{Flagicon|Japan}} [[Wataru Murofushi]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} [[Gabriel Vasconcelos (footballer, born 1996)|Gabriel Vasconcelos]]\n|{{Flagicon|Japan}} [[Fugo Segawa]]\n|{{Flagicon|Jamaica}} Nicholas Hamilton\n|{{Flagicon|Peru|football}} [[Adri\u00e1n Ugarriza]]\n|{{Flagicon|Brazil}} [[Jac\u00f3 (footballer)|Jac\u00f3]]\n|{{Flagicon|Argentina}} Brian L\u00f3pez\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 Canadian Championship]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n{{2020 Canadian Premier League season by team}}\n{{Canadian Premier League}}\n{{2020 in Canadian soccer}}\n{{2019\u201320 in North and Central America, and Caribbean football (CONCACAF)}}\n<!-- {{2020\u201321 in North and Central America, and Caribbean football (CONCACAF)|state=collapsed}}-->\n\n[[Category:2020 Canadian Premier League| ]]\n[[Category:Canadian Premier League seasons]]\n[[Category:2020 in Canadian soccer|Canadian Premier League]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Canadian Premier League]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Canadian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = Canadian Premier League\n| dates      = TBD 2020<br>(regular season)\n| prevseason = [[2019 Canadian Premier League season|2019]]\n| nextseason = ''2021''\n| season = 2020\n}}\nThe '''2020 Canadian Premier League season''' is the second season of the [[Canadian Premier League]], the [[Canadian soccer league system|top level]] of [[Soccer in Canada|Canadian soccer]]. [[Forge FC]] are the defending league champions after defeating [[Cavalry FC]] in the [[2019 CPL Finals]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportingnews.com/ca/soccer/news/forge-fc-wins-inaugural-canadian-premier-league-title/1f1dlbmunre2x18d3hgeghzzt7|title=Forge FC wins inaugural Canadian Premier League title|website=www.sportingnews.com|language=en-ca|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2020, as part of measures to [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|reduce the spread of COVID-19]], the CPL issued a statement announcing a 14-day hold on all pre-season training, effective immediately.<ref name=\"COVID-19\">{{cite web |title=Canadian Premier League Statement: Coronavirus (COVID-19) Protocol for Pre-Season Training |url=https://canpl.ca/article/canadian-premier-league-statement-coronavirus-covid-19-protocol-for-pre-season-training |website=Canadian Premier League |accessdate=March 14, 2020 |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> On March 20, the league announced that it would be postponing the start of the season from the previously scheduled date of April 11.<ref>{{cite web |title=Canadian Premier League Commissioner Statement: Start of season postponed |url=https://canpl.ca/article/canadian-premier-league-statement-on-covid-19 |website=Canadian Premier League |accessdate=March 20, 2020 |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Overview ==\n=== Teams ===\nThe seven teams that participated in the inaugural [[2019 Canadian Premier League season]] are set to compete in this season. They are joined by [[Atl\u00e9tico Ottawa]], an expansion team who were created after the [[USL Championship]] side [[Ottawa Fury FC]] suspended operations after being unable to secure approval from USSF and CONCACAF.<ref>{{cite web |title=Canadian Premier League awards 1st Expansion Team to Ottawa |url=https://canpl.ca/article/canadian-premier-league-awards-1st-expansion-team-to-ottawa |website=Canadian Premier League |accessdate=January 29, 2020 |date=January 29, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.narcity.com/sports/ca/on/ottawa/ottawa-fury-fc-is-over-and-the-team-wont-be-playing-anymore|title=Ottawa's Soccer Team Was Just Cancelled But Fans Want Them To Switch Leagues|website=www.narcity.com|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/canadian-premier-league-ottawa-expansion-2020-rumour/|title=Rumour: Ottawa On Fast-Track To CPL Expansion|last=Jacques|first=John|date=January 15, 2020|website=Northern Tribune|url-status=live|access-date=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Stadiums and locations ====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n![[Atl\u00e9tico Ottawa]]\n![[Cavalry FC]]\n![[FC Edmonton]]\n![[Forge FC]]\n|-\n|[[TD Place Stadium]]\n|[[ATCO Field]]\n|[[Clarke Stadium]]\n|[[Tim Hortons Field]]\n|-\n|[[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]]\n|[[Foothills County|Foothills County, Alberta]]\n|[[Edmonton|Edmonton, Alberta]]\n|[[Hamilton, Ontario]]\n|-\n| Capacity: '''24,000'''\n| Capacity: '''6,000'''\n| Capacity: '''5,100'''\n| Capacity: '''10,116'''{{efn|Artificially reduced from 23,218.}}\n|-\n| [[File: TDPlace.jpg|180px]]\n| [[File: Section_203_ATCO_Field.jpg|180px]]\n| [[File:Clarke Stadium.jpg|180px]]\n| [[File:Tim Hortons Field - Main Grandstand.JPG|180px]]\n|-\n!colspan=4 rowspan=1|\n{{Location map+ |Canada |float=center |caption= |width=450|places=\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=45.4215296 |long=-75.69719309999999 |label_size=85 |label=[[Atl\u00e9tico Ottawa]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=43.2500|long=-79.8667 |label_size=85 |label=[[Forge FC|Forge]]|position=left}}\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=51.044270|long=-114.062019 |label_size=85 |label=[[Cavalry FC|Cavalry]]}}\n{{Location map~ |Canada |lat=48.443056|long=-123.519444 |label_size=85 |label=[[Pacific FC|Pacific]]|position=top}}\n{{Location map~ |Can